DIRECTORY OF NEBRASKA DAIRY CATTLE BREEDERS AND DEALERS. BY J. H. FHANDMN.* lii response to the oft-repeated inquiry, "Where can I par <hase dairy cattle." the Dairy Department of the University of Nebraska has prepared the following directory. Efforts nave been made to secure the name of each and every dealer and breeder of dairy cattle in the State. The names of breeders of l«>th pure-bred and grade stock have been listed so that the farmer wishing to buy pure-bred sires or cows of recognised ability ro produce may have the opportunity of a varied selection. Since the Department has secured the names of breeders and •lealers largely by i-orrespondence, it does not vouch for nor rec - ommend any special one above another and would suggest that personal investigation be made before purchasing. An earnest effort was made to list every breeder in this State. Some names have doubtless been omitted because of the failure of persons to respond to our inquiries or because no information concerning their stork was available. In spite of this, it is the most complete directory of dairy cattle breeders and dealers ever published in this State and as such it should be a step in the right direction. By an examination of the maps in the directory, one can see at ■ glance the numbers which represent dealers and breeders in any given locality. By referring to these numbers in the direc - tory, the name and address of each dealer and breeder may be found. Nebraska is "coming into her own" in the dairy business. With the steadily increasing prices of land and feed stuffs, farm en» are beginning to realize that dairying is one of the solutions of successful farming. It is with this idea in mind that the Dairy Department of the University of Nebraska wishes to be of whatever assistance it can to the farmers of the State in aiding them to secure a better class of dairy cattle. The Department's desire is to promote closer cooperation between our dairy breed ers and prospective purchasers of dairy cattle. The Department will gladly give such information as it may possess concerning any dealer and. whenever possible, will render assistance to any one desiring to build up a better dairy herd. • Credit is due Messrs. E. D. Comstock, Jr.. and H. R. Campbell for careful and conscientious assistance in compiling this directory. EXTENSION BUL. NO. SB. AOR. EXP. STATION OF NEBKA8KA.
